        • Other evolution points: IPX4 splash-proof performance. Enjoy music without worrying about rain or sweat. Integrated processor V1 improves connection stability and battery performance Main unit battery 8 hours / case charge 12 hours, total 24 hours Also supports smartphone charging
        • Significantly enhanced call performance 4 microphones and sensors conduct advanced audio signal processing

        Dave in Georgia
        3.0 out of 5 stars Overrated and Overpriced
        Reviewed in the United States on July 7, 2023
        Color: Platinum SilverStyle: 2021 Model WF-1000XM4Pattern: 1) Each itemVerified Purchase
        The fit was not good mainly because the ear tips are too stiff, they don't conform well to the ear. Also, most of the weight of the ear pods is outside the ear, giving a feeling that they'll easily fall out at any moment. The sound quality for music was quite good, but even on Vocal EQ settings, the sound quality for voice calls was quite poor. Microphone sensitivity is also poor, much more complaints from my callers than with my previous AirPods Pro. I really like that you can have them simultaneously paired with 2 devices without having to forget one and add the other. The texture of the ear pods and the case is quite cheap. It feels like cardboard although it's some type of plastic material. Also, you can't tell the charge status of the ear pods or the case unless you take the ear pods out of the case, a bit inconvenient.

        So, after a few days of experimenting with them in various situations, I'm heading back to a new pair of AirPods Pro, 2nd Generation. The Airpods Pro not having EQ is a drawback, and during the two year life, I had one of the airpods replaced twice under warranty. The third failure would have been on my nickel, and I'm not willing to pay more than 50% of the price of new just to replace one. A $29 Apple Care policy gives me a second year of coverage and other benefits, so back to the old tried and true.
